description: Test for continuity between the battery terminals and the power supply module output terminals to verify if the internal wiring or battery contacts have failed, preventing the delivery of 12V to the circuit., outcome='Continuity test results show a short (R≈0 Ω) from the battery to both the PSU Output Cable (+) and PSU Output Cable (−), indicating intact wiring with no detected breaks between the battery and PSU output terminals. No polarity inversion detected in cable labeling according to the described test paths.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=70.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Power supply module battery case and battery terminals,
description: With the new battery in place, directly measure the voltage at the battery terminals INSIDE the battery case (not at the output cables) to confirm that 12V is present at the battery itself., outcome='The measurement at the battery terminals inside the case shows a voltage of 12.0 V between positive and negative, confirming that 12 V is present at the battery itself. No polarity inversion is indicated in this measurement.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Power supply module battery contacts and wiring connections,
description: Visually inspect the battery contacts and internal wiring connections inside the power supply module for signs of corrosion, loose connections, or physical defects., outcome='No corrosion, loose connections, or physical defects were observed on the battery, LED, or resistors. Both the PSU Output Cable (+) and PSU Output Cable (−) are present, connected, and each is reported to have an internal short circuit with the other. No polarity inversion is indicated in these connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=70.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
